This case has not been concluded. Unless a judgment of conviction is entered, the defendant is presumed innocent of all charges.

Notice to employers: It may be a violation of state law to discriminate against a job applicant because of an arrest or conviction record. Generally speaking, an employer may refuse to hire an applicant on the basis of a conviction only if the circumstances of the conviction substantially relate to the particular job. For more information, see Wisconsin Statute 111.335 and the Department of Workforce Development's publication, Arrest and Conviction Records under the Law.

records.addlTxt: Defendant failing to appear, Court ordered a Bench Warrant to be issued REMAND TO COMMISSIONER. Court takes no action on bail at this time.

Defendant Darlene Chambers not in court.  Attorney Amanda R. Kremer in court for Darlene Chambers.  Prosecuting attorney Gregg Herman in court for the State of Wisconsin. 
Case in court for Calendar Call. 
Defendant failing to appear, Court ordered a Bench Warrant to be issued REMAND TO COMMISSIONER. Court takes no action on bail at this time.

Attorney Amanda R. Kremer in court.  Erika Strebel appeared for the State of Wisconsin.
Case in court for a calendar call. Defendant did not appear due to personal reasons put on the record. Defense requests to reschedule.
Case adjourned.  Calendar call scheduled for August 24, 2022 at 11:00 am.

Attorney Amanda R. Kremer in court.  Erika Strebel appeared for the State of Wisconsin via Zoom.
Case set for status conference.  No appearance by the defendant.  Court ordered a bench warrant issued but stayed until the next court date.  Case adjourned to Br. 30.  Calendar call scheduled for August 4, 2022 at 01:30 pm.
At the request of defense and court's approval, case has been rescheduled. Parties notified.  Status conference scheduled for July 15, 2022 at 01:30 pm.
Received and Filed by Attorney Krermer.
Order to show cause hearing on May 23, 2022 at 08:30 am.

Defendant Darlene Chambers in court.  Navjot Singh Hira appeared for the State of Wisconsin. Case in court for status of counsel. Counsel was unavailable. The Court set status conference by Zoom.  Status conference scheduled for June 9, 2022 at 08:30 am.
Order appointing counsel and criminal complaint emailed to Attorney Kremer.

Defendant Darlene Chambers in court.  Adam Joseph Best appeared for the State of Wisconsin.
Indigency hearing proceeded.  Based upon the defendant's statements, the court found the defendant eligible for appointment of counsel at county expense.  The court appointed Attorney Amanda Kremer to represent the defendant; counsel to be paid at the rate of $100.00 per hour. The court ordered the defendant to repay Milwaukee County for attorney fees at the rate of $30.00 per month beginning on 08-01-2022 and then the 1st of each month there after.  Failure to make timely payments according to the imposed payment schedule may result in a civil judgment, subject to tax intercept. Order Appointing Attorney at County Expense signed and filed.  Status conference scheduled for May 13, 2022 at 01:30 pm.
Defendant appears in person. Defendant to appear on an in-person day. Case remains calendared in Br. 30.  Pre-trial conference scheduled for April 25, 2022 at 08:30 am.

DEFENDANT WAS ORDERED BY THE COURT TO REPORT TO THE MILWAUKEE COUNTY JAIL (CJF) TO BE BOOKED AND RELEASED BY 5:00 P.M. ON (04/02/2022). IF THEY FAIL TO APPEAR A BENCH WARRANT WILL BE ISSUED FOR THEIR ARREST.

Signed and filed, No Contact Order.  Defendant to have no contact with Jessie J.B.
Court advised defendant that failure to comply with conditions of bail may result in an additional charge of bail jumping.

Defendant Darlene Chambers in court.  Mallory R Davis appeared for the State of Wisconsin.
Defendant is advised that this case is assigned to Judge Richards, Branch 30. Court reviewed the complaint and found probable cause. Defendant received a copy of the complaint and was advised of right to counsel. Defendant does not qualify for Public Defender representation. Court entered a plea of not guilty on behalf of the Defendant. Court reserves Defendant's right to file a substitution of judge pursuant to Sec. 971.20 right to challenge probable cause and to have complaint read until Defendant's next scheduled court appearance. Case is adjourned for a Pretrial Conference in Branch 30.  Pre-trial conference scheduled for April 21, 2022 at 08:30 am.
Summons mailed.  Defendant ordered into room 221 Safety Building on 3/31/22 @ 1:30p
